                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Pharaphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-08-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that the foreign office has informed him that the Chinese
                    Government assumes no responsibility for the boycott; that the movement was
                    started by the traders; and that it has taken action as a proof of friendship.
                    The local authorities have again been instructed by telegraph to publish
                    proclamations, to urge the people to attend to their own private affairs, and if
                    any disturbances occur to stop them.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
